                    <ECUC-PARAM-CONF-CONTAINER-DEF>
                      <SHORT-NAME>JWQ3399StateConfig</SHORT-NAME>
                      <DESC>
                        <L-2 L="EN"></L-2>
                      </DESC>
                      <LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>1</LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>
                      <UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>1</UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>
                      <MULTIPLICITY-CONFIG-CLASSES>
                        <ECUC-MULTIPLICITY-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                          <CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
                          <CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-POST-BUILD</CONFIG-VARIANT>
                        </ECUC-MULTIPLICITY-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                        <ECUC-MULTIPLICITY-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                          <CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
                          <CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-VARIANT>
                        </ECUC-MULTIPLICITY-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                      </MULTIPLICITY-CONFIG-CLASSES>
                      <PARAMETERS>
                        <ECUC-INTEGER-PARAM-DEF>
                          <SHORT-NAME>ComTimeOutSet</SHORT-NAME>
                          <DEFAULT-VALUE>0</DEFAULT-VALUE>
                          <LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>1</LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>
                          <UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>1</UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>
                          <VALUE-CONFIG-CLASSES>
                            <ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                              <CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
                              <CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-POST-BUILD</CONFIG-VARIANT>
                            </ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                            <ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                              <CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
                              <CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-VARIANT>
                            </ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                          </VALUE-CONFIG-CLASSES>
                          <SYMBOLIC-NAME-VALUE>false</SYMBOLIC-NAME-VALUE>
                          <MAX>7</MAX>
                          <MIN>0</MIN>
                          <DESC>
                            <L-4 L="EN">Sets the communication timeout. When this timer expires, the device sets the FAULT_SYS1[COMM_TIMEOUT] bit. When this timer expires, the device takes the action 
configured by the [COMM_TIMEOUT_CTRL] bit. The timer resets if device receives command or response in NORMAL mode. 
000 = Disables communication timeout (default at reset); 
001 = 2ms; 
010 = 5ms; 
011 = 10ms; 
100 = 20ms; 
101 = 30ms; 
110 = 60ms; 
111 = 100ms</L-4>
                          </DESC>
                        </ECUC-INTEGER-PARAM-DEF>
                        <ECUC-INTEGER-PARAM-DEF>
                          <SHORT-NAME>InactiveTimeoutSet</SHORT-NAME>
                          <DEFAULT-VALUE>0</DEFAULT-VALUE>
                          <LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>1</LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>
                          <UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>1</UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>
                          <VALUE-CONFIG-CLASSES>
                            <ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                              <CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
                              <CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-POST-BUILD</CONFIG-VARIANT>
                            </ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                            <ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                              <CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
                              <CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-VARIANT>
                            </ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                          </VALUE-CONFIG-CLASSES>
                          <SYMBOLIC-NAME-VALUE>false</SYMBOLIC-NAME-VALUE>
                          <MAX>7</MAX>
                          <MIN>0</MIN>
                          <DESC>
                            <L-4 L="EN">A timeout in NORMAL mode. This timer starts counting when device has no activities(cell balancing and cell measurement) in NORMAL. When the timer expires, the device enters SLEEP/SHIP mode 
depends SLEEP_SHIP_CTRL. The timer resets if device is active in NORMAL mode. 
000 = No timeout. Device remains in NORMAL mode 
001 = 2 s; 
010 = 5 s; 
011 = 10 s 
100 = 30s; 
101 = 1 min (default at reset); 
110 = 10 min; 
111 = 30 min</L-4>
                          </DESC>
                        </ECUC-INTEGER-PARAM-DEF>
                        <ECUC-INTEGER-PARAM-DEF>
                          <SHORT-NAME>InactiveSleepTimeOut</SHORT-NAME>
                          <DEFAULT-VALUE>0</DEFAULT-VALUE>
                          <LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>1</LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>
                          <UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>1</UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>
                          <VALUE-CONFIG-CLASSES>
                            <ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                              <CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
                              <CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-POST-BUILD</CONFIG-VARIANT>
                            </ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                            <ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                              <CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
                              <CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-VARIANT>
                            </ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                          </VALUE-CONFIG-CLASSES>
                          <SYMBOLIC-NAME-VALUE>false</SYMBOLIC-NAME-VALUE>
                          <MAX>7</MAX>
                          <MIN>0</MIN>
                          <DESC>
                            <L-4 L="EN">A timeout in SLEEP mode. This timer starts counting when device enters SLEEP mode and no activities (cell balancing). When the timer expires, the device enters SHIP mode if 
SLEEP_SHIP_CTRL=0. The timer resets when device wakes up to NORMAL mode or the device has activity in SLEEP mode. 
000 = No timeout. Device remains in SLEEP mode (default at reset) 
011 = 1 min 
100 = 10 min 
101 = 30 min 
110 = 1 hour 
111 = 2 hour</L-4>
                          </DESC>
                        </ECUC-INTEGER-PARAM-DEF>
                        <ECUC-INTEGER-PARAM-DEF>
                          <SHORT-NAME>CycleTimeSleepToHB</SHORT-NAME>
                          <DEFAULT-VALUE>0</DEFAULT-VALUE>
                          <LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>1</LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>
                          <UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>1</UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>
                          <VALUE-CONFIG-CLASSES>
                            <ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                              <CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
                              <CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-POST-BUILD</CONFIG-VARIANT>
                            </ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                            <ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                              <CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
                              <CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-VARIANT>
                            </ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                          </VALUE-CONFIG-CLASSES>
                          <SYMBOLIC-NAME-VALUE>false</SYMBOLIC-NAME-VALUE>
                          <MAX>15</MAX>
                          <MIN>0</MIN>
                          <DESC>
                            <L-4 L="EN">The cycle time of the device goes to HEARTBEAT mode from SLEEP. 
(This time is for the top stack device using, other devices use two times of t the timeout of tcyc_HB_TO) 
0000 = disable HEARTBEAT mode (default) 
0001 = disable HEARTBEAT mode (reserved) 
0010 = disable HEARTBEAT mode (reserved) 
0011 = 50 milliseconds 
0100 = 100 milliseconds 
0101 = 200 milliseconds 
0110 = 300 milliseconds 
0111 = 500 milliseconds 
1000 =1 second. 
1001 = 2 seconds. 
1010 = 4 seconds. 
1011 = 8 seconds. 
1100 = 12 seconds. 
1101 = 16 seconds. 
1110 = 32 seconds. 
1111 = 64 seconds</L-4>
                          </DESC>
                        </ECUC-INTEGER-PARAM-DEF>
                        <ECUC-ENUMERATION-PARAM-DEF>
                          <SHORT-NAME>SLEEP_SHIP_CTRL</SHORT-NAME>
                          <DESC>
                            <L-4 L="EN">This bit is to set the lowest power-consumption and regular mode for the device. 
0: The lowest power-consumption and regular mode for the device is SHIP mode (default) 
1: The lowest power-consumption and regular mode for the device is SLEEP mode (In this mode, the 
device goes to SHIP only when there are some faults)</L-4>
                          </DESC>
                          <LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>1</LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>
                          <UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>1</UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>
                          <DEFAULT-VALUE>GetsIntoSHIP</DEFAULT-VALUE>
                          <VALUE-CONFIG-CLASSES>
                            <ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                              <CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
                              <CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-POST-BUILD</CONFIG-VARIANT>
                            </ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                            <ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                              <CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
                              <CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-VARIANT>
                            </ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                          </VALUE-CONFIG-CLASSES>
                          <LITERALS>
                            <ECUC-ENUMERATION-LITERAL-DEF>
                              <SHORT-NAME>GetsIntoSHIP</SHORT-NAME>
                              <ORIGIN>AUTOSAR_ECUC</ORIGIN>
                              <DESC>
                                <L-4 L="EN">This bit is to set the lowest power-consumption and regular mode for the device. 
0: The lowest power-consumption and regular mode for the device is SHIP mode (default) 
1: The lowest power-consumption and regular mode for the device is SLEEP mode (In this mode, the 
device goes to SHIP only when there are some faults)</L-4>
                              </DESC>
                            </ECUC-ENUMERATION-LITERAL-DEF>
                            <ECUC-ENUMERATION-LITERAL-DEF>
                              <SHORT-NAME>GetsIntoSLEEP</SHORT-NAME>
                              <ORIGIN>AUTOSAR_ECUC</ORIGIN>
                              <DESC>
                                <L-4 L="EN">This bit is to set the lowest power-consumption and regular mode for the device. 
0: The lowest power-consumption and regular mode for the device is SHIP mode (default) 
1: The lowest power-consumption and regular mode for the device is SLEEP mode (In this mode, the 
device goes to SHIP only when there are some faults)</L-4>
                              </DESC>
                            </ECUC-ENUMERATION-LITERAL-DEF>
                          </LITERALS>
                        </ECUC-ENUMERATION-PARAM-DEF>
                        <ECUC-ENUMERATION-PARAM-DEF>
                          <SHORT-NAME>COMM_TIMEOUT_CTRL</SHORT-NAME>
                          <DESC>
                            <L-4 L="EN">1: The device gets into SLEEP when communication timeout occurs. 
0: The device gets into SHIP when communication timeout occurs. (default)</L-4>
                          </DESC>
                          <LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>1</LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>
                          <UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>1</UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>
                          <DEFAULT-VALUE>SHIP</DEFAULT-VALUE>
                          <VALUE-CONFIG-CLASSES>
                            <ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                              <CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
                              <CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-POST-BUILD</CONFIG-VARIANT>
                            </ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                            <ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                              <CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
                              <CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-VARIANT>
                            </ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                          </VALUE-CONFIG-CLASSES>
                          <LITERALS>
                            <ECUC-ENUMERATION-LITERAL-DEF>
                              <SHORT-NAME>SHIP</SHORT-NAME>
                              <ORIGIN>AUTOSAR_ECUC</ORIGIN>
                              <DESC>
                                <L-4 L="EN">1: The device gets into SLEEP when communication timeout occurs. 
0: The device gets into SHIP when communication timeout occurs. (default)</L-4>
                              </DESC>
                            </ECUC-ENUMERATION-LITERAL-DEF>
                            <ECUC-ENUMERATION-LITERAL-DEF>
                              <SHORT-NAME>SLEEP</SHORT-NAME>
                              <ORIGIN>AUTOSAR_ECUC</ORIGIN>
                              <DESC>
                                <L-4 L="EN">1: The device gets into SLEEP when communication timeout occurs. 
0: The device gets into SHIP when communication timeout occurs. (default)</L-4>
                              </DESC>
                            </ECUC-ENUMERATION-LITERAL-DEF>
                          </LITERALS>
                        </ECUC-ENUMERATION-PARAM-DEF>
                      </PARAMETERS>
                    </ECUC-PARAM-CONF-CONTAINER-DEF>
                    <ECUC-PARAM-CONF-CONTAINER-DEF>
                      <SHORT-NAME>JWQ3399BalanceConfig</SHORT-NAME>
                      <DESC>
                        <L-2 L="EN"></L-2>
                      </DESC>
                      <LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>1</LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>
                      <UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>1</UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>
                      <MULTIPLICITY-CONFIG-CLASSES>
                        <ECUC-MULTIPLICITY-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                          <CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
                          <CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-POST-BUILD</CONFIG-VARIANT>
                        </ECUC-MULTIPLICITY-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                        <ECUC-MULTIPLICITY-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                          <CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
                          <CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-VARIANT>
                        </ECUC-MULTIPLICITY-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                      </MULTIPLICITY-CONFIG-CLASSES>
                      <PARAMETERS>
                        <ECUC-BOOLEAN-PARAM-DEF>
                          <SHORT-NAME>OTCBEnable</SHORT-NAME>
                          <DEFAULT-VALUE>false</DEFAULT-VALUE>
                          <LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>1</LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>
                          <UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>1</UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>
                          <VALUE-CONFIG-CLASSES>
                            <ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                              <CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
                              <CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-POST-BUILD</CONFIG-VARIANT>
                            </ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                            <ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                              <CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
                              <CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-VARIANT>
                            </ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                          </VALUE-CONFIG-CLASSES>
                          <DESC>
                            <L-4 L="EN">Enable the OTCB detection of external thermistors during cell balancing. The selection is sampled whenever [BAL_GO] = 1 is set by the host. 
0 = disable OTCB detection (default) 
1 = enable OTCB detection 
Note: The OTCB protection is only enabled when the GPIOx are set as ADC input &amp; OTUT1 or ADC input &amp; OTUT2.</L-4>
                          </DESC>
                        </ECUC-BOOLEAN-PARAM-DEF>
                        <ECUC-INTEGER-PARAM-DEF>
                          <SHORT-NAME>CellBalanceStopThreshold</SHORT-NAME>
                          <DEFAULT-VALUE>0</DEFAULT-VALUE>
                          <LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>1</LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>
                          <UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>1</UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>
                          <VALUE-CONFIG-CLASSES>
                            <ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                              <CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
                              <CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-POST-BUILD</CONFIG-VARIANT>
                            </ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                            <ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                              <CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
                              <CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-VARIANT>
                            </ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                          </VALUE-CONFIG-CLASSES>
                          <SYMBOLIC-NAME-VALUE>false</SYMBOLIC-NAME-VALUE>
                          <MAX>121</MAX>
                          <MIN>0</MIN>
                          <DESC>
                            <L-4 L="EN">If a cell’s voltage &lt; this threshold, the cell balancing on that cell stops. This threshold setting applies to all the cells. 
0x00 = Disable voltage comparison for cell balancing done threshold 
0x01 = 2000 mV. 
0x02 = 2025 mV. 
… 
0x78 = 4975 mV. 
0x79 = 5000 mV.</L-4>
                          </DESC>
                        </ECUC-INTEGER-PARAM-DEF>
                      </PARAMETERS>
                      <SUB-CONTAINERS>
                        <ECUC-PARAM-CONF-CONTAINER-DEF>
                          <SHORT-NAME>OTCBThresholds</SHORT-NAME>
                          <DESC>
                            <L-2 L="EN"></L-2>
                          </DESC>
                          <LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>0</LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>
                          <UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>1</UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>
                          <MULTIPLICITY-CONFIG-CLASSES>
                            <ECUC-MULTIPLICITY-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                              <CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
                              <CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-POST-BUILD</CONFIG-VARIANT>
                            </ECUC-MULTIPLICITY-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                            <ECUC-MULTIPLICITY-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                              <CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
                              <CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-VARIANT>
                            </ECUC-MULTIPLICITY-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                          </MULTIPLICITY-CONFIG-CLASSES>
                          <PARAMETERS>
                            <ECUC-INTEGER-PARAM-DEF>
                              <SHORT-NAME>OTCBThreshold1</SHORT-NAME>
                              <DEFAULT-VALUE>0</DEFAULT-VALUE>
                              <LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>1</LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>
                              <UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>1</UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>
                              <VALUE-CONFIG-CLASSES>
                                <ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                                  <CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
                                  <CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-POST-BUILD</CONFIG-VARIANT>
                                </ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                                <ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                                  <CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
                                  <CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-VARIANT>
                                </ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                              </VALUE-CONFIG-CLASSES>
                              <SYMBOLIC-NAME-VALUE>false</SYMBOLIC-NAME-VALUE>
                              <MAX>15</MAX>
                              <MIN>0</MIN>
                              <DESC>
                                <L-4 L="EN">Set the OTCB threshold1 of the external thermistors for the OTUT comparator when BAL_CTRL1[OTCB_EN] = 1. The MCU shall configure the corresponding GPIO(s) to “ADC &amp; OTUT 
input”. The PTC or NTC ranges are selected by the DEV_CONF2[PTC_EN] register. 
[PTC_EN] = 0: 
0b0000-0b0101 = Range from 5% to 10% in steps of 1% (NTC). 
0b0110-0b1100 = Range from 12% to 24% in steps of 2% (NTC). 
0b1101-0b1111 = Reserved (24%) (NTC). 
[PTC_EN] = 1: 
0b0000-0b0111 = Range from 56% to 63% in steps of 1% (PTC). 
0b1000-0b1111 = Reserved (63%) (PTC).</L-4>
                              </DESC>
                            </ECUC-INTEGER-PARAM-DEF>
                            <ECUC-INTEGER-PARAM-DEF>
                              <SHORT-NAME>OTCBThreshold2</SHORT-NAME>
                              <DEFAULT-VALUE>0</DEFAULT-VALUE>
                              <LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>1</LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>
                              <UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>1</UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>
                              <VALUE-CONFIG-CLASSES>
                                <ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                                  <CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
                                  <CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-POST-BUILD</CONFIG-VARIANT>
                                </ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                                <ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                                  <CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
                                  <CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-VARIANT>
                                </ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                              </VALUE-CONFIG-CLASSES>
                              <SYMBOLIC-NAME-VALUE>false</SYMBOLIC-NAME-VALUE>
                              <MAX>15</MAX>
                              <MIN>0</MIN>
                              <DESC>
                                <L-4 L="EN">Set the OTCB threshold2 of the external thermistors for the OTUT comparator when BAL_CTRL1[OTCB_EN] = 1. The MCU shall configure the corresponding GPIO(s) to “ADC &amp; OTUT 
input”. The PTC or NTC ranges are selected by the DEV_CONF2[PTC_EN] register. 
[PTC_EN] = 0: 
0b0000-0b0101 = Range from 5% to 10% in steps of 1% (NTC). 
0b0110-0b1100 = Range from 12% to 24% in steps of 2% (NTC). 
0b1101-0b1111 = Reserved (24%) (NTC). 
[PTC_EN] = 1: 
0b0000-0b0111 = Range from 56% to 63% in steps of 1% (PTC). 
0b1000-0b1111 = Reserved (63%) (PTC).</L-4>
                              </DESC>
                            </ECUC-INTEGER-PARAM-DEF>
                            <ECUC-INTEGER-PARAM-DEF>
                              <SHORT-NAME>OTCBThreshold3</SHORT-NAME>
                              <DEFAULT-VALUE>0</DEFAULT-VALUE>
                              <LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>1</LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>
                              <UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>1</UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>
                              <VALUE-CONFIG-CLASSES>
                                <ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                                  <CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
                                  <CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-POST-BUILD</CONFIG-VARIANT>
                                </ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                                <ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                                  <CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
                                  <CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-VARIANT>
                                </ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                              </VALUE-CONFIG-CLASSES>
                              <SYMBOLIC-NAME-VALUE>false</SYMBOLIC-NAME-VALUE>
                              <MAX>15</MAX>
                              <MIN>0</MIN>
                              <DESC>
                                <L-4 L="EN">Set the OTCB threshold3 of the external thermistors for the OTUT comparator when BAL_CTRL1[OTCB_EN] = 1. The MCU shall configure the corresponding GPIO(s) to “ADC &amp; OTUT 
input”. The PTC or NTC ranges are selected by the DEV_CONF2[PTC_EN] register. 
[PTC_EN] = 0: 
0b0000-0b0101 = Range from 5% to 10% in steps of 1% (NTC). 
0b0110-0b1100 = Range from 12% to 24% in steps of 2% (NTC). 
0b1101-0b1111 = Reserved (24%) (NTC). 
[PTC_EN] = 1: 
0b0000-0b0111 = Range from 56% to 63% in steps of 1% (PTC). 
0b1000-0b1111 = Reserved (63%) (PTC).</L-4>
                              </DESC>
                            </ECUC-INTEGER-PARAM-DEF>
                            <ECUC-INTEGER-PARAM-DEF>
                              <SHORT-NAME>OTCBHysteresis</SHORT-NAME>
                              <DEFAULT-VALUE>0</DEFAULT-VALUE>
                              <LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>1</LOWER-MULTIPLICITY>
                              <UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>1</UPPER-MULTIPLICITY>
                              <VALUE-CONFIG-CLASSES>
                                <ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                                  <CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
                                  <CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-POST-BUILD</CONFIG-VARIANT>
                                </ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                                <ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                                  <CONFIG-CLASS>PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-CLASS>
                                  <CONFIG-VARIANT>VARIANT-PRE-COMPILE</CONFIG-VARIANT>
                                </ECUC-VALUE-CONFIGURATION-CLASS>
                              </VALUE-CONFIG-CLASSES>
                              <SYMBOLIC-NAME-VALUE>false</SYMBOLIC-NAME-VALUE>
                              <MAX>7</MAX>
                              <MIN>0</MIN>
                              <DESC>
                                <L-4 L="EN">Set the OTCB hysteresis of the external thermistors for the OTUT comparator when BAL_CTRL2[OTCB_EN] = 1 
0b000=5mV 
0b001=10mV 
0b010=15mV 
0b011=20mV 
0b100=25mV 
0b101=30mV 
0b110=35mV 
0b111=40mV</L-4>
                              </DESC>
                            </ECUC-INTEGER-PARAM-DEF>
                          </PARAMETERS>
                        </ECUC-PARAM-CONF-CONTAINER-DEF>
